# Omarchy / Arch Linux "Brewfile" equivalent
#
# Omarchy is Arch-based, so:
# - Official repos: `pacman`
# - Community packages: AUR via an AUR helper (usually `yay` or `paru`)
#
# This file is intentionally a *declarative list* (not executable).
# You can install from it with something like:
#
#   # pacman packages
#   awk '/^## pacman$/{f=1;next} /^## /{f=0} f && $0 !~ /^($|#)/{print}' linux/Brewfile \
#     | xargs -r sudo pacman -S --needed --noconfirm
#
#   # AUR packages (requires yay or paru)
#   awk '/^## aur$/{f=1;next} /^## /{f=0} f && $0 !~ /^($|#)/{print}' linux/Brewfile \
#     | xargs -r yay -S --needed --noconfirm
#
# Notes:
# - Package names can differ slightly across Arch repos/AUR; treat this as a starting point.
# - Some macOS-only casks have no direct Linux equivalent; see the notes section.

## pacman
# base tooling / build (AUR helpers often need these)
base-devel
git

# CLI tools (mapped from your macOS Brewfile)
bat
curl
csvkit
difftastic
git-delta
