zsh
zsh-autosuggestions
zsh-syntax-highlighting

# Languages / formatters / linters (names can vary; keep what exists in repos)
eslint

# Apps that usually exist in Arch repos
obsidian
spotify-launcher
telegram-desktop

## aur
# JS tooling typically via AUR
eslint_d
prettierd

# Dev tools / apps (AUR)
cursor-bin
google-chrome
ghostty-bin

# Fonts (closest to your Homebrew cask font)
ttf-meslo-nerd-font-powerlevel10k

# Zsh theme (if you prefer package-managed theme over git clone)
zsh-theme-powerlevel10k

# Zen Browser (Firefox fork) â€“ package name may vary; adjust if needed
zen-browser-bin

# WhatsApp desktop (choose one; names vary in AUR)
whatsapp-for-linux

## notes
# macOS-only (no-op on Linux / replaced by Omarchy/Hyprland defaults)
# - aerospace (macOS tiling WM) -> Hyprland already covers this
# - alfred -> consider `rofi-wayland` or `wofi` (not listed here to keep parity-focused)
# - finicky -> consider `xdg-utils` + per-app URL handlers (or `handlr`), plus browser profiles
# - hiddenbar -> use your bar (Waybar) config instead
#
# Optional Omarchy/Wayland quality-of-life (not in your macOS Brewfile but often useful)
# - grim, slurp, wl-clipboard (screenshots + clipboard)
# - waybar (status bar)
# - rofi-wayland / wofi (launcher)


